The South African of the Year Awards 2016 Postponed, organisers announced on Monday.ANN7 announced that the South African of the Year (SATY) Awards 2016 will be postponed until 2017. The postponement is due to unforeseen regulatory circumstances that have materially impacted on logistics for the event. Regretfully this has left us with no choice but to seek a new date in the near future. We look forward to confirming a rescheduled date, the Channel said.Launched in 2014 by the news channel ANN7, the SATY s are an awards ceremony dedicated to celebrating South Africa s greatest musicians, artists, conservationists, sport, youth and business leaders alike.A new date will be announced in due course.TNA Reporter